"Axis along which the medians are computed. The default (None) is to compute "
"the median along a flattened version of the array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/ma/extras.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ma.extras.median:18
msgid "**out**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/ma/extras.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ma.extras.median:-1
msgid "ndarray, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/ma/extras.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ma.extras.median:16
msgid ""
"Alternative output array in which to place the result. It must have the same "
"shape and buffer length as the expected output but the type will be cast if "
"necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/ma/extras.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ma.extras.median:27
msgid "**overwrite_input**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/ma/extras.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ma.extras.median:-1
msgid "bool, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/ma/extras.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ma.extras.median:21
msgid ""
"If True, then allow use of memory of input array (a) for calculations. The "
"input array will be modified by the call to median. This will save memory "
"when you do not need to preserve the contents of the input array. Treat the "
"input as undefined, but it will probably be fully or partially sorted. "
"Default is False. Note that, if `overwrite_input` is True, and the input is "
"not already an `ndarray`, an error will be raised."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/ma/extras.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ma.extras.median:34
msgid "**keepdims**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/ma/extras.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ma.extras.median:30
msgid ""
"If this is set to True, the axes which are reduced are left in the result as "
"dimensions with size one. With this option, the result will broadcast "
"correctly against the input array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/ma/extras.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ma.extras.median:0
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

